        "title": "Why does my UnicodeFont (Slick2D) not draw?",
        "body": "<p>So I am trying to draw a font using Slick2D's UnicodeFont. The code that loads the font:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Font font = new Font(\"Arial\", Font.BOLD, 20);\nUnicodeFont uFont = new UnicodeFont(font);\nuFont.addAsciiGlyphs(); \nuFont.getEffects().add(new ColorEffect(java.awt.Color.BLACK));\nuFont.loadGlyphs();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>It's more or less copied and pasted from the wiki. Next, during a frame I use gluOrtho2d() and reset the projection and modelview matrices. Then I call <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>this.font.drawString(100, 50, \"some text goes here\");\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>to actually draw the text. But all I get is an empty screen, an no errors of any kind.<\/p>\n",
